<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   ASDF Chief on Nuclear Verification Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ASDF Chief on Nuclear Verification Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206184194 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2206184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In his lecture to students of the MAINICHI SHIMBUN 
Businessmen's College at a hotel in Makubari, Chiba city, Isao 
Ishizuka, Air Self-Defense Force chief of staff, touched on the 
issue of North Korea's suspected development of nuclear weapons 
and said it is necessary to bring North Korea's past nuclear 
developments to light. Commenting on the U.S. Government's tilt 
toward freezing the DPRK's current nuclear program, he said: 
"My personal view is that freezing North Korea's nuclear 
program alone is not enough. As a neighboring nation of the 
DPRK, Japan will not be satisfied with freezing North Korea's 
nuclear program without verifying that country's past nuclear 
developments." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

