<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Leaves for ROK Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Leaves for ROK Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306065594 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306065594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The station correspondent reported from the Royal 
Thai Air Force Headquarters airport that Prime Minister Chuan 
Likphai and his delegation left Bangkok this morning for an 
official visit to the Republic of Korea from 23-26 June at the 
invitation of President Kim Yong-sam of the Republic of Korea. 
  High-level dignitaries in the entourage include Deputy Prime 
Minister Amnuai Wirawan, Deputy Prime Minister Suphachai 
Phanitchaphak, Foreign Affairs Minister Squadron Leader Prasong 
Sunsiri, Defense Minister General Wichit Sukmak, and Deputy 
Commerce Minister Chaiyot Sasomsap, as well as a group of 14 
businessmen. 
  The main aim of the visit is to strengthen and further 
develop the existing relations and cooperation between Thailand 
and the Republic of Korea, especially in the economic and 
political fields, as well as cooperation in this region. 

</TEXT>

