<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Receives Japanese Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Receives Japanese Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2206145394 Hanoi VNA in English 1424 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2206145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 22 -- Deputy Prime Minister [P.M.] 
Tran Duc Luong received here this afternoon a delegation of the 
Japanese Government led by Director of the Foreign Ministry 
Shigekazu Sato now on a working visit to Vietnam. 
  Speaking to his guests, Deputy P.M. Tran Duc Luong said that 
the multi-faceted cooperation between Vietnam and Japan has 
recently seen fine steps of development. He stressed that the 
two countries would further strengthen their bilateral relations 
and make positive contributions to the cause of development in 
the Asian-Pacific region for peace, friendship and cooperation. 
Deputy Prime Minister Luong highly appreciated the Japanese 
Government's valuable assistance to Vietnam, especially the 
Official Development Assistance (ODA). He also expressed his 
wish for the further consolidation and development of the 
cooperation of mutual benefits between Vietnam and Japan. 
  For his part, Mr. S. Sato noted that the aim of the Japanese 
delegation's visit is to exchange views with concerned officials 
of the Vietnamese Government to promote the economic cooperation 
between the two countries in the form of ODA loan. He highly 
valued the important achievements recorded by the Vietnamese 
people in their cause of socio-economic development. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

