<H3> <TI>   Military Delegation Concludes DPRK Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Delegation Concludes DPRK Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2206150494 Hanoi VNA in English 1447 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2206150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 22 -- The Vietnamese high-ranking 
military delegation led by Gen. Doan Khue, politburo member of 
the Communist Party of Vietnam Central Committee (CPVCC) 
yesterday left Pyongyang concluding a week-long official 
friendship visit to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea 
(DPRK). 
  While there, the Vietnamese military delegation was received 
by President of the DPRK and General Secretary of the Korean 
Workers' Party Central Committee (KWPCC) Kim Il Sung. It also 
had talks with a DPRK high-ranking military delegation. 
  The Vietnamese delegation also toured some units and 
colleges 
of the People's Armed Forces of the DPRK and a number of 
socio-economic establishments and scenery in Pyongyang and other 
localities. 

</TEXT>

