<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Amends Policy on Censorship </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Amends Policy on Censorship </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306101594 Hanoi QUAN DOI NHAN DAN in Vietnamese 2 Jun 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi QUAN DOI NHAN DAN </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 30 May 1994, the government promulgated Decree 
No. 44-CP amending Article 2 of Decree No. 79-CP dated 6 
November 1993. 
  Under the newly-promulgated decree, Article 2 of Decree No. 
79-CP has been amended as follows: "The state will not censor 
publications before they run off the press, except in cases 
deemed necessary by the prime minister of the government. In 
such cases, the minister of culture and information will bear 
responsibility before the prime minister for the censorship of 
and action against the publications involved." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

