<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Wants AMC Individuals Punished </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Wants AMC Individuals Punished </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306094994 Hanoi NHAN DAN in Vietnamese 7 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BK2306094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi NHAN DAN </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Recently, the Dong Nai Province Agricultural 
Materials Corporation imported 40 tonnes of poor quality DK888 
corn strains from Thailand for sale to peasants in Xuan Loc 
District, Dong Nai Province, causing heavy losses to production. 
  After reviewing a report by the Government Office and the 
action taken by the Ministry of Agriculture and Food Industry 
and the Dong Nai Province people's committee, the prime minister 
of the Government instructed the people's committee to prepare a 
detailed report on the case to determine the responsibility of 
the Agricultural Materials Corporation [AMC] for the imports and 
sale of poor quality corn strains to peasants, take appropriate 
disciplinary action against those individuals involved, and 
adopt urgent practical measures to ensure the interests of the 
peasants. 
  The prime minister also instructed the people's commitee to 
direct the Agricultural Materials Corporation in contacting the 
Thai exporter to resolve this problem. 
  Following this incident, the prime minister instructed state 
management agencies and organs and units in charge of supplying 
agricultural materials countrywide to uphold a sense of 
responsibility in preventing a recurrence of such an incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

