<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Keating: No Need To Raise Interest Rates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Keating: No Need To Raise Interest Rates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306081894 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Paul Keating, has again said 
the government sees no need for an increase in official interest 
rate arguing that such a rise would only generate new wage 
claims. But as speculation continues over a possible rise 
Federal Opposition Leader Alexander Downer has attacked the 
prime minister's record on financial management. 
  [Begin Downer recording] I would make the point that it was 
Mr. Keating as the treasurer who deregulated financial markets 
and wanted Australia to operate in this deregulated environment 
and there's no point in him turning around, now having 
deregulated financial markets and attacking those financial 
markets for not agreeing with him. [End recording] 

</TEXT>

