<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Directive on Seeking Early Inter-Korean Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Directive on Seeking Early Inter-Korean Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2306002894 Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN in Korean 23 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2306002894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Kim Pong-son] </F>
  [Text] On the morning of 23 June, the government will hold 
an emergency meeting of the Unification-National Security Policy 
Coordination Council headed by Chairman Yi Hong-ku, deputy prime 
minister and minister of the National Unification Board, to 
fine- tune its final position before it takes future 
countermeasures in the wake of North Korea's acceptance of our 
proposal for a preliminary contact for the summit talks. 
  In particular, the government will decide on which three 
delegates will represent our side at the preliminary contact and 
notify the North Korean side of the list. 
  The government has temporarily designated Deputy Prime 
Minister Yi as the head delegate. It has been learned that the 
government will select two vice ministerial-level officials as 
other delegates. 
  It has also been learned: President Kim Yong-sam gave 
directives that the government see to it that the summit meeting 
is realized as soon as possible, regardless of time or place. 
In this connection, the government will work towards finalizing 
its policy to realize summit talks in July. 

</TEXT>

