<H3> <TI>   Clinton Calls Kim on Resumption of DPRK Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clinton Calls Kim on Resumption of DPRK Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2206235794 Seoul YONHAP in English 2353 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2206235794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 23 (YONHAP) -- U.S. President Bill 
Clinton phoned South Korean President Kim Yong-sam Thursday 
morning and discussed concerted measures on the North Korean 
nuclear dispute. 
  Clinton called Kim at 7:57 AM and explained the background 
behind the U.S. decision to agree to resume a third round of 
high-level talks with North Korea. 
  Kim, for his part, explained the progress of Seoul's 
preparations for the proposed inter-Korean summit meeting. The 
two leaders exchanged views on steps to take with regard to the 
North Korean nuclear issue. 

</TEXT>

