<H3> <TI>   DPRK Invites Seoul Sports Officials to Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Invites Seoul Sports Officials to Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2306105794 Seoul YONHAP in English 1033 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2306105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 23 (YONHAP) -- North Korea has invited 
South Korean sports officials to a meeting this weekend to 
discuss the second East Asia games slated for Sept. 20 next year 
in Pyongyang. 
  An official at the Korean Amateur Sports Association (KASA) 
said on Thursday that the Pyongyang East Asia Games Organizing 
Committee extended the invitation to KASA, informing that the 
Pyongyang games' eighth consultative meeting would be held in 
Taipei on June 26-28. 
  The message dated May 25 was delivered through the Taiwan 
Olympic Committee. A copy of the message was later sent to the 
Korean Olympic Committee [KOC] via the Chinese Olympic 
Committee, the official said. 
  Originally North Korea planned to hold the eighth meeting in 
Japan during the Hiroshima Asian games period. But, at the 
suggestion by games member countries that it would be too late, 
North Korea advanced the time of the meeting to this weekend, a 
sports source said. 
  In response to the invitation, KASA would send three 
delegates including Pak Sang-ha, KOC International Committee 
chairman, to the Taipei meeting, the official added. 

</TEXT>

