  [Text] Seoul, June 23 (YONHAP) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan 
Likphai arrived in Seoul Thursday afternoon aboard a special 
Thai Air Force plane for a four-day official visit at the 
invitation of President Kim Yong-sam. 
  The Thai premier was greeted by Foreign Minister Han 
Sung-chu 
on arrival at Seoul airport. 
  On Friday morning, Prime Minister Chuan and President Kim 
will have a summit meeting at Chongwadae [presidential offices] 
to exchange opinions on East Asia situations centered on the 
nuclear question. 
  Later in the day, Chuan will meet with Prime Minister Yi 
Yong-tok and National Assembly Speaker Yi Man-sop. In the 
evening, he will attend a dinner to be hosted by President and 
Mrs. Kim. 
  Chuan is the first Thai prime minister to visit Seoul since 
1981. 

