<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Minister Comments on WTO Post Bid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Minister Comments on WTO Post Bid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2306100394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0746 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2306100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 23 (YONHAP) -- Trade, Industry and 
Energy Minister Kim Chol-su said Thursday he feels a strong 
sense of responsibility to run for the post of secretary-general 
of the World Trade Organization (WTO). 
  "It's a great honor that the Korean Government has 
recommended me as a candidate for the position, but at the same 
time I feel a heavy responsibility to compete for the post at 
the world organization which is called the United Nations of the 
economy," Kim said in an interview. 
  He explained that the new WTO secretary-general is entitled 
to officially launch the trade body next Jan. 1 or at the 
earliest possible date thereafter. 
  The new secretary-general, he continued, should also push 
for 
negotiations on the service sector that are still pending after 
the Uruguay Round. 
  In addition, the group's chief must exercise leadership in 
solving the myriad world trade problems linked to the 
environment, economic policies, labor standards and technology 
policies, he noted. 

</TEXT>

