<H3> <TI>   President Kim Discusses Competitiveness </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Kim Discusses Competitiveness </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2306103294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1009 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2306103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 23 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
called on leading company presidents Thursday to take the lead 
in building up the nation's international competitiveness and 
bringing about smooth labor-management relations. 
  At a Chongwadae [presidential offices] luncheon he hosted 
for 
28 company presidents, Kim stressed that for labor-management 
harmony, good human relations should be maintained between the 
two sides and companies should be managed clean-handedly without 
any spot of suspicion. 
  Presidential spokesman Chu Ton-sik quoted the president as 
telling the attendees that Korean industries should increase 
competitiveness through technological development and 
productivity elevation. 
  Industries should also respect the order of fair competition 
and establish firm industrial ethics, the president said. 
  Among the attending company heads were Pae Sun-hun, 
president 
of Daewoo Electronics Co.; Yi Tae-won, president of Samsung 
Aerospace Co.; and Kim Chu-yong, president of Hyundai 
Electronics Co. 

</TEXT>

