Prime Minister Hata and SDPJ Chairman Murayama are set to hold a 
top-level meeting at 2100 this evening. The ruling coalition 
parties and the SDPJ are likely to resume their talks at 1100 
tomorrow morning after seeing the results of their top-level 
meeting. 
  The ruling coalition parties and the SDPJ held three rounds 
of talks this morning, this afternoon, and this evening. During 
the talks, they came closer to agreeing that an extraordinary 
Diet session must be called as soon as possible to pass a bill 
on demarcating the single-seat constituencies, but they failed 
to reach an agreement on the question of handling the tax system 
reform. (end recording) 

