<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Thanks Workers for Unity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Chong-il Thanks Workers for Unity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2106055994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0408 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2106055994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of 
the Korean People's Army Comrade Kim Chong-il sent thanks to 
many units and working people including the Sunan District, 
Pyongyang municipality, committee of the Workers' Party of Korea 
[WPK], the Songyo District Garment Office in Pyongyang, the 
Segori Senior Middle School in Pyongyang, the Pukchang County, 
South Pyongan Province, committee of the WPK, the hot rolling 
shop of the Kim Chaek Iron and Steel Complex and Kim Myong-chol, 
a cameraman of the physical science library of the state 
commission of physical culture and sports, for their full 
display of the traditional traits of army-people unity. 
  In the DPRK where the tradition of army-people unity is in 
full bloom, the army and the people are defending the socialist 
motherland, closely rallied behind the party and the leader in 
one mind and purpose. 
  Upon receiving the thanks, the officials of the units and 
working people are hardening their determination to bring about 
a new turn in the performance of their revolutionary assignments 
and better their assistance to the People's Army. 

</TEXT>

