<DOCNO> FBIS4-30106 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas121_c_94022" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-121 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yi In-mo Tours Sites Around Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yi In-mo Tours Sites Around Pyongyang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2106060394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0425 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2106060394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- Former war 
correspondent of the Korean People's Army Yi In-mo, the 
incarnation of faith and will, visited the exhibition of the 
three revolutions in Pyongyang. 
  Being briefed on the brilliant achievements made by the 
Korean people in carrying on the three revolutions, ideological, 
technical and cultural, under the wise leadership of the party 
and the leader, he saw with deep emotion exhibits at the general 
hall, the heavy industry hall, the light industry hall and other 
halls. 
  After his visit, he said that the Korean people have brought 
a great change in socialist economic construction under the 
party's unique banner of the three revolutions. The exhibition 
well shows the economic development of the country which is 
demonstrating its might to the whole world, he noted. 
  "Our country", he stressed, "could build a solid independent 
national economy with a powerful chuche-based industry and 
developed agriculture because it was under the tested guidance 
of the great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il". 
  At the end of his visit to the West Sea Barrage, he wrote in 
the visitor's book: 
  "This barrage fully shows the matchless grit of the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il and the looks of the Korean people 
united around him in one mind. 
  Yi In-mo toured the revolutionary site on Munsu Hill and the 
Grand People's Study House in Pyongyang. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

