<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Farmers Urge Senate Not To Ratify GATT </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Farmers Urge Senate Not To Ratify GATT </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2306082194 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2306082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Filipino farmers are asking the Philippine Senate 
not to ratify the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade or 
GATT, which government representatives signed in Marrakech, 
Morocco recently. The farmers said the agreement would deepen 
rural poverty, hunger, and joblessness. The farmers spoke 
during a hearing yesterday at the Senate on GATT. 
  Senator Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo, chairperson of the 
committees on trade and commerce, said her committees will hold 
judgment on GATT until all sectors are heard. She said the 
Senate set October as the deadline for acting on GATT to enable 
the Philippines to catch up with the implementation of the 
accord. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

