<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   War Veterans Delegation Visits U.S., France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    War Veterans Delegation Visits U.S., France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2206132394 Hanoi VNA in English 1401 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2206132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 18 -- A delegation of the Vietnam War 
Veterans's Association led by Sr. Lt. Gen. Tran Van Quang 
president of the association, paid a working visit to the United 
States and France from mid-May to early June. 
  The visit came at the invitation of the president of the 
International Committee for Fund Raising for the Construction of 
`Vietnam's Van Canh Friendship Village', the mayor and the Santa 
Cruz City Council, California, the US, and the French War 
Veterans, and Invalids Association Arac-France and the Marseille 
chapter of the Vietnamese's Association in France. 
  While in the US, the Vietnamese delegation attended a 
conference of the fund-raising committee held in Santa Cruz, 
California, with the participation of representatives from 
Britain, Germany, the US, Japan, and France aimed at stepping up 
preparation for the construction of the village. It also took 
part in a round-table meeting on veterans' reconciliation in the 
presence of US veterans from different localities. 
  In France, the Vietnamese delegation attended a ceremony 
held 
in Marseille to mark President Ho Chi Minh's birthday. In 
Paris, it took part in an international conference of the 
veterans' organizations of Britain, Bulgaria, Germany, Hungary, 
Russia, France, Slovakia and Vietnam. 
  It also attended a meeting in support of the construction of 
the Van Canh Friendship Village. 

</TEXT>

