<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kakizawa Cancels U.S. Visit To Meet Kantor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kakizawa Cancels U.S. Visit To Meet Kantor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2306113094 Tokyo KYODO in English 1122 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2306113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 23 KYODO -- Foreign Minister Koji 
Kakizawa has canceled a planned visit to the United States this 
weekend for bilateral "framework" trade talks with U.S. Trade 
Representative Mickey Kantor, a high-ranking Foreign Ministry 
official said Thursday [23 June]. 
  The cancellation was decided because the main opposition 
Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) submitted a no-confidence motion 
earlier in the day to the House of Representatives against the 
cabinet of Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata, the official said. 
  If the lower house approves the motion, Hata must either 
resign with his entire cabinet or dissolve the house for a 
general election. 
  "Under the circumstances, it is not appropriate for the 
foreign minister, who is a member of the cabinet, to go to the 
U.S. and negotiate," the official said. 
  Kantor said Tuesday he plans to discuss macroeconomic and 
sectoral issues when he meets Kakizawa. 
  On Tuesday, Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai said 
Kakizawa's visit to the U.S. has yet to be fixed because of 
uncertainties in Japan's political community. 
  Kakizawa was to leave Japan on Friday and return to Tokyo on 
Monday. 
  Japan and U.S. officials have said they hope to reach an 
agreement in the talks on setting up a new bilateral trade 
framework before the Naples summit of the Group of Seven (G-7) 
industrial nations in July. 
  Under the framework negotiations designed to rectify the 
chronic trade imbalance between the two countries, the U.S. is 
pressing Japan to set "objective criteria" to measure progress 
in market- opening. 
  But Tokyo rejects binding criteria, saying they could lead 
to 
managed trade. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-30114 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas121_a_94002" </HT>


