BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 23 KYODO -- Foreign Minister Koji 
Kakizawa informed U.S. Trade Representative Mickey Kantor by 
phone on Thursday [23 June] night that he has canceled his 
planned visit to the United States this weekend for bilateral 
"framework" trade talks, Foreign Ministry officials said. 
  Kakizawa and Kantor agreed to hold a working-group meeting 
on 
the framework talks in the middle of next week in Washington, 
the officials said. 
  The cancellation was decided because the main opposition 
Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) submitted a no-confidence motion 
earlier in the day to the House of Representatives against the 
cabinet of Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata, they said. 

