<H3> <TI>   Namchongnyon Protests Reported in ROK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Namchongnyon Protests Reported in ROK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2206055294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0439 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2206055294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["S. Korean Students Slam Campus Suppression" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 22 (KCNA) -- About 200 students of 
Chonnam National University of South Korea formed an Emergency 
Measure Committee to denounce the search of campuses and defend 
the Kwangju-South Cholla Provincial Federation of General 
Student Councils (Namchongnyon) on June 19 before launching an 
all-night sit-in strike, a radio report from Seoul said. 
  The students strongly denounced the puppet authorities for 
hurling police into their university, walking away students and 
perpetrating search and confiscation for the mere reason that 
students in this area went to Seoul to participate in a people's 
rally to check the "parliamentary endorsement of the Uruguay 
Round accord" and held protests. 
  The students pointed out that the puppet authorities' 
suppression is aimed at disuniting the Namchongnyon, and 
demanded an immediate release of their fellow students. 

</TEXT>

