<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-121 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK Military `Provocations' in DMZ Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Military `Provocations' in DMZ Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2306111694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1043 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2306111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["South Korean Bellicose Elements Perpetrate Military </F>
Provocations" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 23 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
bellicose elements perpetrated military provocations again in 
the Demilitarized Zone (DMZ), military sources said. 
  They illegally introduced recoilless guns into the southern 
portion of the DMZ in the central sector of the front from June 
20 to 22. 
  They also brought by stealth large-caliber machine guns into 
the MP [military police] posts in the central sector of the 
front and in the eastern sector of the front. 
  On June 22, they brought 25 vehicles and 500 armed personnel 
into the southern portion of the DMZ to build military setups. 
  If the South Korean bellicose elements continue aggravating 
the tensions in the DMZ despite our repeated warnings, they will 
have to bear full responsibility for all consequences arising 
therefrom. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

