<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   DSP Head on Hata Cabinet Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DSP Head on Hata Cabinet Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2406092894 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 23 Jun 
94 Evening Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2406092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The opposition Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] is 
poised to submit a no-confidence motion against the Hata cabinet 
to the Diet. Commenting on the LDP's move at a 23 June meeting 
of members of the House of Representatives and the House of 
Councillors who are affiliated with the ruling Democratic 
Socialist Party [DSP], DSP Chairman Takashi Yonezawa pointed 
out: "If the no- confidence motion against the Hata cabinet is 
approved in the Diet, then the Hata cabinet would resign en 
masse, leaving no possibility of Prime Minister Hata becoming 
again prime minister." He went on to say, "the Hata cabinet 
should think of its voluntary general resignation while watching 
as the LDP submits a no-confidence motion to the Diet." He also 
stated that the Hata cabinet should study the possibility of 
resigning en masse depending on the outcome of talks with the 
opposition Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] on forming a 
new coalition and the SDPJ's internal situation. 

</TEXT>

