  [Text] Pyongyang, June 22 (KCNA) -- The National Alliance 
for Democracy and Reunification in South Korea issued a 
statement denouncing the Kim Yong-sam fascist clique's 
suppression of the South Korean Federation of General Student 
Councils (Hanchongnyon), a South Korean newspaper reported. 
  The statement said the suppression of Hanchongnyon angers 
the 
people as it is an anti-national act. 
  The inaugural ceremony of the second-term Hanchongnyon as a 
reasonable independent mass organisation was a very legitimate 
meeting, said the statement, adding that the invocation of the 
"National Security Law" charging Hanchongnyon with the "tendency 
toward benefiting the enemy" is an open suppression to stifle 
Hanchongnyon. 

